Description: Golden Pine Ventures is a venture capital firm that seeks out biotechnology and biomedical opportunities developed by researchers and grows them into valuable businesses. The firm is based in Durham, North Carolina and also provides consulting services.
Gray Ventures was a venture capital firm that invested in the information technology industry. The firm was founded in 1991 and was based in Atlanta, Georgia.
Empty

GreenHills Ventures is a private investment holding company established in 2001 for the purpose of investing in early stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in the healthcare technology, medical devices, mobile, wireless and cloud software sectors. It is based in New York, New York.
Heroic Ventures is an early stage venture capital firm. The firm was founded in 2016 and is based in Palo Alto, California.

Hickory Venture Capital is a corporate venture arm of First Tennessee Bank National Association. The firm prefers to invest in the healthcare services, medical devices, information technology, telecommunications, non-technology, basic manufacturing and service sectors. It was founded in 1985 and is based in Huntsville, Alabama.
Hippo Ventures is a Raleigh, North Carolina based venture capital firm. The firm seeks to invest in the technology and healthcare sectors.

Honeycomb Ventures is a venture capital firm which seeks to invest in global media, technology and telecommunication companies, including those that focus on the cloud computing, payments, security technology and e-commerce sectors.

Highgate Ventures is the corporate venture arm of Igate based in Westport, Connecticut. The firm is focused on early stage technology investments in the hospitality industry. It seeks to invest in the internet infrastructure, enterprise software and e-services sectors.

Huntington Ventures is a venture capital fund investing predominantly in seed, early and later stages. The firm prefers to invest in the communication, digital, media, mobility, innovation and software sectors. It was founded in 2000 and is based in Irvine, California.

Ignite Venture Partners provides capital and consulting services to the companies operating in the consumer internet, consumer products, retail, telecommunication, mobile, medical and healthcare sectors. The firm is based in Scottsdale, Arizona and was established in 2003.
InHouse Ventures is a boutique investment fund that focuses on building and acquiring multi-generational, impact oriented brands. The firm is based in Healdsburg, California.

Invest Illinois Venture Fund is a venture capital firm operated by Department of Commerce and Economic Opportunity, Government of Illinois. The firm seeks to invest in the agriculture, food, clean energy, information technology, biotechnology, manufacturing, medical devices, nanotechnology, telecommunications, transportation and logistics sectors.

iYa Ventures is a Community Development Venture Capital firm that is identifying, investing and advising startups with technology-based solutions in Sub-Saharan Africa. It is a member of the Community Development Venture Capital Association, which has over 20 years of promoting the use of the tools of venture capital to advance the livelihoods of low-income people and the economies of distressed communities.
IOC Ventures is a venture capital firm that focuses on supporting the earliest stage founders and their teams. It is based in Irvine, California.

Kapyon Ventures, LLC is a San Diego based incubation firm focused on the development of technology spinouts from global research institutes. Kapyon's areas of focus include agricultural biotechnology, industrial biotechnology and cleantech. Kapyon works closely with both domestic and international research partners across New Zealand, Australia and Canada, and through these partnerships manages an investment portfolio of several biotechnology joint ventures.

Johnson Ventures is a venture capital and private equity firm based in Columbus, Indiana. The firm seeks opportunities for the acquisition of a business to hold for long term growth. It invests in companies operating in the business and consumer products and services sector.

KICventures is a private equity and venture capital firm in the health technology sector that specializes in creating ecosystems for connecting patients and surgeons. Within the health technology sector, the firm focuses on the areas of healthcare services, consumer electronics, medical devices and consumer healthcare.

KBL Healthcare Ventures is a venture capital firm which invests in start-up, early-Stage and emerging growth companies. The company targets the healthcare sectors which includes Biopharmaceuticals, Drug Discovery, Medical Devices and Health Care Services. The firm also considers investment in Information Technology. The firm is based in New York, New York and was founded in 1991.

Kirlan Venture Capital (KVC) is a Seattle-based venture capital firm. The firm invested in early to mezzanine stage companies in the healthcare, life sciences, internet, software, communications, specialty retail, manufacturing and other technology sectors.

Kolohala Ventures, founded in 2006, is an early-stage venture capital firm committed to investing in Hawaii companies. It believes that Hawaii is extremely well positioned to become the "green lab of the Pacific." Hawaii has strategic advantages in specific sectors: Renewable Energy, Life and Ocean, IT, Media/Film, and Kolohala is positioned to exploit these advantages. Hawaii's economy, environment, public policy, and investment community are converging to create a promising new hot spot for "green" investing.
Kodak Ventures Group is a corporate venture capital investment arm of Eastman Kodak. The firm prefers to invest primarily in the wireless technology sector.
Legacy Ventures International is an impact investor that focuses on acquisitions of proven and high-potential businesses across a variety of business sectors. The firm is based in Las Vegas, Nevada.

Leslie Ventures is a venture capital firm. The firm is based in Portola Valley, California and was founded in 2001.

Landmark Ventures is a strategic and financial advisory firm offering a combination of venture development and global investment banking services, with a focus on serving growth oriented technology companies and their venture capital and private equity sponsors. Landmark offers years of experience providing services in the areas of mergers and acquisitions, private placements, business development, revenue and market development, direct investments and strategic advisory.

Linn Grove Ventures is a venture capital management firm based in Fargo, North Dakota. The firm makes strategic investments in early to mid-stage companies with outstanding growth capability. It was founded in 2010.
Liquid Venture Partners is a venture capital firm which specializes in seed, early stage and later stage investments. The firm is based in Marina del Rey, California.

Lira Venture Capital is an angel investment firm supporting and financing start-ups and early-stage companies. The firm prefers investing in seed, angel, venture rounds and also provides micro loans of between $5,000 and $100,000. It also acts as an accelerator providing entrepreneurs with office space with furniture, office equipment and related services.

Maniv Bioventures was a venture capital firm founded in 1997. The firm made its investments in drug discovery, devices, biotechnology, pharmaceuticals and life sciences sectors.

McKenna Ventures is a venture capital firm that specializes in investments, consulting, sponsorships and programs in a variety of industries. The firm invests in early stage businesses that operate in the food, beverage and technology sectors. It was established in 2009 and is based in Chicago, Illinois.

MVP is exclusively focused on funding the discovery and clinical application of treatments and cures for neuromuscular diseases. Adapting elements of the venture capital model, the MVP business plan is characterized by an emphasis on measurable results along with deep involvement by its scientific and industry advisers. MVP evaluates and makes targeted investments in for-profit and not-for-profit companies and academics developing therapeutics for neuromuscular diseases. It is based in Chicago, Illinois.

MedScience Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Boston, Massachusetts. The firm seeks to invest in the life science and medical technologies sectors. It seeks to partner with early stage companies to provide consulting services, obtain license rights in specific markets, and evaluate making equity investments.

The firm is ardently focused on finding innovative entrepreneurs in China, India and the United States, concentrating mainly on information technology, consumer opportunities (devices, software, silicon, web), converged media and entertainment and wireless opportunities.

Minor Ventures is a San Francisco based venture capital firm. The firm primarily seeks to invest in early-stage technology and media companies.

Mosaix Ventures is a venture capital firm investing in healthcare innovation and special situations. The firm prefers to invests in early- to mid-stage specialty or niche businesses and also medical devices and healthcare information technology & services sectors.

Oceanshore Ventures is a venture capital firm which invests in early stage private companies. The company focuses on the renewable energy, energy storage and energy efficiency based technologies sectors. It was founded n

Pacific Community Ventures is a growth equity fund which provides capital and resources to high growth California businesses operating in the specialty food products, ethnic products and services, health and wellness, manufacturing, and environmentally-friendly focused product sectors. Pivotal's philosophy is to go early and ground-breaking, with a focus on preclinical or pre-proof of concept therapeutics, from discovery through to phase 1 of clinical development and will be centered on life sciences in the United States and Europe. It was established in 2017 and was created by the Nan Fung Group, a Chinese property developer in Hong Kong.

PacRim Venture Partners (PVP) is a private venture capital fund with investors from the United States, Taiwan and Hong Kong. The firm focus their investments on early-stage information technology companies in Silicon Valley.

The firm invests in early-stage and growth-stage energy innovations in renewable energy, clean technology, energy conversation, green materials and other clean technologies. Quicksilver Ventures is a venture capital firm based in Saratoga, California that seeks to invest in computing and consumer technology. The firm focuses on advising and raising institutional capital for early and growth-stage healthcare and environmental science companies in the healthcare IT, medical devices, biotech, waste conversion and water treatment technologies sectors.

Rock Ventures is the umbrella entity that provides operational coordination, guidance and integration of Quicken Loans Founder Dan Gilbert’s portfolio of companies, investments and real estate purchases. Santa Fe Venture Partners is a General Partner with the Silicon Valley based venture capital firm International Venture Fund I. IVF I is a seed and early stage Venture Capital group with investments in California, Arizona, Utah, Hawaii, and New Mexico.

Saratoga Ventures is a venture capital firm which specializes in seed, early and later stage investments. The firm prefers to invest in companies based in San Francisco operating in the healthcare, biotechnology, pharmaceuticals and health technology sectors. The program includes professional level laboratories, equipment, tools and work suites. Shore Ventures II, a subsidiary of Hershey Management, is a venture capital firm headquartered in New York City, focuses on providing growth and expansion capital to talented entrepreneurs to build great businesses and ultimately achieve a successful liquidity event. The investment focus is on late seed, series A and B financing rounds

SEED Venture Finance, LLC is a private investment firm specializing in subordinated debt, senior debt and equity investments in small and medium sized businesses. SEED has established strategic partnerships with major commercial banks in the region and is uniquely positioned to provide a company with a full range of capital raising options and related services.

In the life sciences sector, the firm invests in medical devices, bio therapeutics, specialty diagnostics, bioinformatics and healthcare information technology. Snow Ventures is an early stage investment management firm which provides diversification exposure to systemic and market risks. It was founded in 2015 and is based in San Francisco, California.

Spangler Ventures is a venture capital firm which seeks to invest in the manufacturing, mobile, clean technology, financial technology, energy, financial services and information technology industries. The firm is based in Seattle, Washington and was founded in 1982.

Springboard Venture Fund is an independent sponsor formed to invest in companies emerging from the Springboard Enterprises accelerator programs. T2 Venture Capital is a venture capital firm that invests in startup and early stage technology based companies.
Empty

True Wealth Ventures is a venture capital firm that seeks to invest in women-led companies with products and technologies in the consumer health and sustainable consumer sectors. The firm's investment thesis is that women-led companies perform better financially, yet are an untapped market for investors since only 3% of venture dollars go to women-led start-ups and 15% to those with a woman on the leadership team. In addition, since women make 85% of consumer purchase decisions and 80% of healthcare decisions, it believes there is an additional advantage for companies with women on the management team in designing products for, selling to and servicing these women customers in these markets.

Tyson New Ventures is the corporate venture arm of Tyson Foods. The firm is focused on making investments into alternative proteins, businesses that seek to eliminate food loss and insecurity and "Internet of Food" technologies that empower consumers to drive performance throughout the food chain. Tyson New Ventures is based in Chicago, Illinois.

Venturehouse Group is a private equity company that creates, builds, invests in and acquires technology companies, with a focus on telecommunications and the Internet. Warbros Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Westerly, Rhode Island. The firm seeks to invest in the beverages, fitness technology, automotive electronics, equine products, fire suppression, consumer finance, security, computer peripherals and printing technology sectors.

Empty

Windward Ventures specializes in early stage companies but it does not invest in seed stage companies. The firm invests in private companies based in Southern California from Santa Barbara to San Diego. The firm typically takes minority stake with board representation in its portfolio companies.

Windamere Venture Partners was a venture capital firm which specialized in start up and early stage investments. The company primarily invested in medical devices, pharmaceuticals and biotechnology companies. It was founded in 1998 and was based in La Jolla, California.

Arconic Ventures is the corporate venture capital arm of Arconic, Inc. As a strategic investor, the firm invests in early stage companies with technology or business models relevant to Arconic's broad interests in materials and manufacturing.

Aqua Ventures is a venture capital firm which specializes in seed, early stage, later stage and growth investments. Coastal Ventures is a venture capital and impact investment firm which aims at serving as a business platform for its various Board, Advisory and Management projects. It is a Delaware corporation, with offices in the central coast area of California.

Dioko Health Ventures is a venture capital firm that prefers to invest in the healthcare and technology startups. The firm was founded in 2014 and has offices in Brentwood, Winston Salem and Charlotte.

Drydock Ventures is a Boston based boutique Private Equity and Venture Capital firm. Dominion Ventures is a venture capital investment based in Walnut Creek, California and was founded in 1985. Hudson Ventures is a venture capital firm based in New York, New York. InnoVentures is a Venture Capital firm and the manager of the UTFC funds. Their portfolio companies are typically early stage information technology or service companies seeking growth capital to fund marketing activities. They are based in Utah, USA.

Leawood Ventures is a venture capital firm and an affiliate of Leawood Capital. The firm invests in businesses from early stage through expansion stage and provides capital, financing, and expertise to facilitate effective scale in sectors well positioned to leverage new technologies and innovation.
Provider of venture capital funding.

Loup Ventures is a research-driven, early stage venture capital firm based in Minneapolis, Minnesota and New York that seeks to invest in companies operating in virtual reality, augmented reality, artificial intelligence and robotics. The firm was founded in 2017.

MASA Life Science Venture is a venture capital firm based in Bethesda, Maryland. The firm seeks to invest in early and growth stage companies operating in the bio-therapeutics, specialty pharmaceutical, medical devices, healthcare and biotechnology sectors.

Najeti Ventures specializes in private equity investments in diverse industries throughout the United States. Najeti Ventures is part of Najeti S.A.S., a family-owned company specializing in private equity in the United States, venture capital in Spain and hospitality services in France. Najeti’s mission encompasses a global commitment to provide capital investment and business support to new or expanding enterprises with the goal of promoting their growth into highly profitable, long-term, sustainable businesses. The foundation of Najeti Ventures' strategy is to identify well-positioned companies in both growing and consolidating industry sectors and support strong management teams to realize their full potential. Actively partnering with other experienced investors, Najeti provides strong origination and transaction expertise throughout the life of the investment. Najeti's areas of interest include recapitalizations, buyouts and growth equity.

Mediphase Venture Partners is a venture capital firm, founded in 1999 and headquartered in Newton, Massachusetts. The firm specializes in early stage investments. It approaches to support entrepreneurs and enable growth by providing capital, financial discipline, resources, business development expertise, and industry knowledge. MFV focuses on regional businesses that operate within a reasonable proximity to middle-Tennessee, but may invest outside of target region when finds businesses with strong potential where it can add particular value.

Princeton Ventures Management is a private equity and venture capital firm that seeks to invest in the business services, consumer products and services, education, entertainment, internet and media, financial services, healthcare, information services and technology sectors. The firm's portfolio companies have ongoing access to the ff Acceleration Team, who provide a full range of services in accounting and finance, publlic relations and branding, engineering, recruiting, community management and business development.

e.ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. Founded in 1998, the firm is an early-stage investor and backs founders in the United States, Europe, Asia and Latin America. The e.ventures team has been investing in internet companies focusing on consumer internet, media and mobile. The company's investments are governed by a board of management. e. ventures uses data science to help find startups to review and to conduct due diligence.

Charles River Ventures is a venture capital firm, founded in 1970 and is based in Cambridge, Massachusetts. The firm prefers to make investments in early stage companies engaged in the communications and technology, enterprise software and services, media and entertainment sectors.

Madrona Venture Group is a venture capital firm based in Seattle, Washington. The firm primarily invests in early stage technology companies within the information technology, e-commerce, digital media and advertising, mobile and infrastructure sectors.

Trinity Ventures is a venture capital firm, founded in 1986 and is based in Menlo Park, California. The firm focuses on seed and early stage companies in the technology sector including cloud, mobile infrastructure, digital media, social commerce and entertainment.

Ignition Venture Partners is a venture capital firm which specializes in seed, early stage and later stage investments. It prefers to invest in companies based in the United States operating in the software, communications and technology sectors. The firm was founded in 1999 and is based in Los Altos, California with an additional office in Seattle, Washington.

Shasta Ventures is a boutique, early-stage venture capital firm based in Menlo Park, California. The firm seeks to invest in disruptive approaches to enterprise and consumer technology, including cloud computing, SaaS, enterprise software, consumer services, marketplaces, ecommerce, mobile and networked devices.

DCM Ventures is a venture capital firm specializing in seed, early stage and later stage investments. The firm seeks to invest in the consumer software and services, communications, clean technology, consumer internet, digital media, mobile, security, storage, content, e-commerce, cloud computing and big data sectors. It was founded in 1996 and is based in Menlo Park, California with additional offices in Tokyo, Japan and Beijing, China.

Atlas Venture is a biotech-focused venture capital firm. Atlas Venture has been building biotech startups since 1993. The firm works with scientists and entrepreneurs to translate high impact science into medicines for patients. Atlas Venture's seed-led venture creation strategy selects and focuses investment on opportunities to build scalable businesses and realize value. Atlas Venture is headquartered in Cambridge, Massachusetts.
AME Cloud Ventures is a venture capital firm that focuses on seed to later stage companies building infrastructure and value chains around data. The firm is based in Palo Alto, California.

Bain Capital Ventures (BCV) provides seed through growth capital for companies focused on technology and technology-enabled services primarily for enterprise customers. BCV invests across sectors including infrastructure software, application software, FinTech and healthcare. As the venture capital affiliate of Bain Capital, a assets firm, BCV has partnered with more than 200 companies since 1984 to start, build, commercialize and grow their businesses. The firm has offices in the Bay Area, New York City and Boston.

Menlo Ventures is a venture capital firm which seeks to invest in the consumer and enterprise technology sectors. Within these two sectors the firm specializes in investing in the areas of ad tech, e-commerce, mobile, gaming, new media, social and web, private communications, internet infrastructure, software, semiconductor, data storage, and computer hardware cloud and SaaS, communication and hardware, security, storage and Big Data.

Felicis Ventures is a boutique venture capital firm which was founded in 2006. The firm specializes in seed, startup, pre-revenue stage, early stage and later stage financing. More than 60 portfolio companies of it have got acquired or gone public.

Slow Ventures is a venture capital firm based in San Francisco, California. The firm was founded in 2009 and seeks to invest in the media, consumer goods and services, software, retail and information technology sectors.

Norwest Venture Partners is a multi-stage venture capital and growth equity investment firm based in Palo Alto, California. The firm prefers to invest in the cloud and IT infrastructure, SaaS and enterprise software, internet and consumer, healthcare, technology, information services, financial services and consumer products sectors.

Lerer Hippeau Ventures is a seed stage venture capital firm which seeks to invest in companies operating in the information technology, media, retail, mobile and manufacturing sectors. LHV was founded in 2010 and is based in New York City, New York.

True Ventures is a venture capital firm that specializes in seed, early stage and later stage investments. It seeks to invest in the education, consumer devices, infrastructure, media, mobile and software sectors. The firm was founded in 2005 and is based in Palo Alto, California with an additional office in San Francisco, California.

Redpoint Ventures is a Menlo Park, California based venture capital firm and was founded in 1999. The firm specializes in early, seed and growth stage investments. The firm focuses on investments in companies within new distribution platforms, next generation media, media distribution business, infrastructure technologies for data processing, enterprise software, cloud and mobile sectors. Redpoint Ventures uses data science capabilities to help find startups to review and to conduct due diligence.

Great Oaks Venture Capital is a venture capital firm which specializes in seed, early stage and later stage investments. The firm prefers to invest in companies based in New York and San Francisco operating in the gaming, consumer mobile, technology, internet, Saas and hardware sectors. It was founded in 2003 and is based in New York, New York.

Qualcomm Ventures is the venture capital arm of Qualcomm and is based in San Diego, California. The firm focuses on investing in companies operating in the communication devices, wireless communications, infrastructure, wireless internet, telecommunications, media and mobile sectors. It was founded in 2000.

Insight Venture Partners is a private equity firm that seeks to invest in the e-commerce, internet, mobile, media, online gaming, software sectors. It provides recapitalization, PIPE, buyouts, expansion, growth and later stage investments. The firm was founded in 1995 and is headquartered in New York with additional offices in the United States, Europe, and Asia.
DreamIt Ventures is a startup accelerator program based in Aston, Pennsylvania. The firm provides the startups with access to investors, a sales pipeline and a network of resources.

Lightspeed Venture Partners is a venture capital firm headquartered in Menlo Park, California. The firm was founded in 2000 and seeks to invest in early stage companies operating in the information technology, big data, cloud solution, storage, networking, consumer, mobile, e-commerce, media and software sectors.

Salesforce Ventures is the corporate venture arm of Salesforce.com. The firm prefers to make seed, early stage and later stage venture investments within the enterprise cloud sector. It primarily invests in companies built on the Salesforce Platform or are listed on AppExchange. It was founded in 2009 and is headquartered in San Francisco, California.

Khosla Ventures is a venture capital firm that focuses on making investments in early and later stage companies as well as seed funding for early-stage companies. The firm seeks to invest in the enterprise, advertising, financial services, semiconductors, health, big data, agriculture/food, sustainable energy and robotics industries, with a particular focus on the internet and clean technology sectors. It was established in 2004 and is headquartered in Menlo Park, California.

Battery Ventures is a venture capital and private equity technology-focused investment firm that invest in the software and services, web infrastructure, consumer internet, mobile and industrial technologies sectors. The firm was founded in 1983 and is based in Boston, Massachusetts.

Founded in 1911, Bessemer Venture Partners is a venture capital firm based in Larchmont, New York. The firm focuses on investing in companies operating in the clean technology, energy, healthcare, financial services, mobile, data security, cloud computing, software, communications and manufacturing sectors.

Google provides search and advertising services, which together aim to organize and monetize the world’s information. In addition to its dominant search engine, it offers a plethora of online tools and platforms including: Gmail, Maps, YouTube, and Google+, the company’s extension into the social space. Most of its Web-based products are free, funded by Google’s highly integrated online advertising platforms AdWords and AdSense. Google promotes the idea that advertising should be highly targeted and relevant to users thus providing them with a rich source of information. Google has also made strong moves into the web-based apps space with acquisitions of Jotspot (documents), 2Web Technologies (spreadsheets) and Zenter (presentations). The company has also made a splash with the acquisitions of YouTube, DoubleClick and Feedburner.

CG Health Ventures provides investment and support to innovative start ups. We have a particular interest in the fields of Health IT, Digital Health and Genomics, where we look for projects that address real needs in attractive markets. We typically invest in the project early, sometimes even at concept stage.
We look for entrepreneurs who have grand ambitions and will not give up easily on achieving their dreams. We believe in the importance of values fit; we want to work effectively together but also have fun along the way.
We prioritize projects to which we can add value through our engagement, passion, experience and network, as we like to roll up our sleeves to support the entrepreneur throughout their journeys.
We think global, but our network and experience is concentrated in Europe and the US.

Description: Rabo Private Equity (RPE) is the investment platform of the Rabobank Group. RPE offers two direct investment activities: Rabo Participaties (RaPar) and Phoenix Recovery Capital (Phoenix) and also manages funds in which Rabo invests (RPE Indirect Funds).RaPar is a captive fund that invests in Dutch SME companies (≥ EUR 1,5m EBITDA). RaPar invests in varied situations, e.g. growth and Management Buy-Outs, and commits to a wide range of sectors and activities (sector agnostic). RaPar invests through cumulative preference share solutions where new investments range from EUR 2m to EUR 15m. Phoenix is a captive fund that offers different equity solutions, e.g. debt-to-equity swaps, for restructuring purposes to support Rabobank clients in distressed circumstances. Thus Phoenix works closely with Special Asset Management (RN BBR) of Rabobank Group. Investments may range from EUR 2m to EUR 10m. RPE Indirect Funds participates in a portfolio of strategic funds focused on specific markets in strategically relevant geographies. Through the indirect funds, Rabobank typically plays an active role as sponsor LP and seeks to leverage Rabobank’s knowledge and network to facilitate value-add where applicable, including Investment and Advisory Committees seats and roles where appropriate.

Description: Rocky Point Ventures was founded in 2006 as a private family office in Austin, Texas. Traditionally, RPV has focused on early-stage investing in technology and biotechnology start-ups. Although RPV continues to make these types of investments, we have also begun to seek buyout opportunities. This website is designed to facilitate this new private equity strategy. As opposed to private equity funds, RPV is an active investor focusing on acquisitions of lower-middle market businesses in the Texas and Southeast regions. RPV is guided by the following principles: Effective use of our experience and contacts. Our team has direct knowledge in a wide variety of industries. If we don't have the experience, we certainly know the person or team who does. Focusing on a small number of deals. Concentrating on fewer deals means more time and energy we can devote to adding value. We believe in growing a business. RPV invests with the intention of increasing market share, not investing in "lifestyle businesses. We deploy "patient capital" with the goal of producing long-term value in our portfolio companies. We are not in the business of flipping companies, and our management style reflects this long-term philosophy.

Description: City Hill Ventures, LLC is a health care focused investment firm based in San Diego, California, one of the leading metropolitan area life science clusters in the world. City Hill Ventures was initially founded to make seed and early stage investments in private companies in life sciences (therapeutics, diagnostics, medical devices) and health care technology. The investment focus is now primarily on private and public biotechnology companies. Our approach to maximizing value is to Found, Fund, and Lead companies. This includes launching a new company around a promising product or technology where we may be a founder ("Found"), investing in the companies we launch or existing companies that already have outstanding management in place ("Fund"), and running or advising our portfolio companies with an active, hands on approach to add value ("Lead"). We focus our capital and expertise on only a select group of portfolio companies at a time, where we may serve on the Board of Directors, in advisory roles, or in key management roles. Our selectivity ensures that all of our companies benefit from a high level of attention, which increases their opportunity to be successful. However, we also invest on an opportunistic basis in companies that already have outstanding management teams in place. Inspired by Matthew 5:14, Jonathan Lim established City Hill Ventures in 2010 to build a San Diego based investment firm that could have a positive impact on health care. At City Hill Ventures, we are entrepreneurs, investors, and C-level executives. Our mission is to restore human health through innovation, by building or helping other health care entrepreneurs build great companies that collectively have a transformative impact on patients, the health care industry, and society.

Description: CLI Ventures is a global venture capital and private equity investment firm dedicated to creating credibility and value in our business relationships and to establishing long-term partnerships with our entrepreneurs, investors, and industry collaborators. The firm invests across the healthcare sector and at all stages of company development, with an emphasis on the discovery and development of novel diagnostics, therapeutics, and data applications. With $1 billion under management and offices in Palo Alto, New York, Boston, San Diego, Los Angeles, Beijing, Shanghai, Shenzhen, and Wuhan. CLI has built a team with deep investment, operating, and scientific expertise that enables a hands-on approach to company building. CLI affiliated funds has been involved in the formation of more than 200 portfolio companies. Our companies have created a number of U.S. and China approved products that have advanced human health. CLI has developed innovative investment models, such as U.S.-China cross-border licensing, which have proven successful and have been widely emulated in the life science industry. CLI is engaged in new collaborations, including CLI's investments in China with the health ministries and departments and local government at city and province levels, respectively. For more information, please visit http://www.cli.ventures.

Description:
MVP ist der Cleantech Venture Capital Spezialist aus München.

Munich Venture Partners konzentriert sich auf Risikokapital für High-Tech Startup-Unternehmen mit wachstumsorientierten und ertragsbringenden Projekten. Das Engagement ist dabei auf Europa und ausgewählte internationale Investments fokussiert. MVP gehört zu den größten Cleantech Venture Capital Spezialisten Deutschlands. Wir sind stolz darauf für die Fraunhofer-Gesellschaft der präferierte Venture Capital Partner zu sein. 

Das Team von MVP – Senior Executives großer internationaler Konzerne und erfahrene Venture Capital Professionals und Unternehmer – hat es sich zur Aufgabe gemacht, Potenziale bei Startups und bei bereits bestehenden Unternehmen zu identifizieren und zu entwickeln.

Da wir durch tiefes Branchen- und Fach-Know als Kapitalgeber Technologie und Marktpotenzial einschätzen können, sind wir auch in der Lage, mit unseren Portfolio-Unternehmen eine entsprechende Wachstumsstrategie zu planen und umzusetzen. MVP begleitet dabei die Gründer professionell mit fundiertem unternehmerischem und fachlichem Knowhow in allen Phasen der Entwicklung - von der ersten Idee bis zum rentablen, langfristigen und nachhaltigen Unternehmen.

Munich Venture Partners wurde 2005 gegründet, hat seinen Sitz in München und ist teilweise über die Europäische Union und deren Programm "Wettbewerbsfähigkeit und Innovation" (CIP) finanziert.
LinkedIn Bio:

Description:
Private Investments in Public Equities

Chicago Venture Partners (CVP) is a leading provider of capital to emerging and growth-stage small cap companies through its private investments in public equities (PIPES) portfolio strategy. We invest our own capital which allows us the flexibility to pursue opportunities across a variety of industry sectors and to provide funding at a pace that meets the portfolio company’s near-term and long-term liquidity needs. We differentiate ourselves from other investment firms in the PIPE space by tailoring the deal structure and investment size to the specific portfolio company. Our deal professionals review the merits of each deal individually allowing us to operate outside the bounds of standard structures, preferred industries and fixed funding amounts.

Other Private Investments

CVP actively looks for opportunities to create long-term value for our wholly owned businesses and the affiliate entities we manage. For established companies, we partner with management to provide the capital and strategic guidance needed to achieve their operational goals. In other instances we will cultivate an idea and combine the right mix of human capital and financial support to build a successful business model. We apply our fundamental belief in innovation, creativity and nurturing potential when researching, analyzing and executing all current and prospective investments.

Description:
Yucatan Rock is an investment and consulting firm co-founded by Stephen G. Pearse and Robert G. Pearse.

Stephen is known for leading one of Silicon Valley’s fastest ever value creation startups. He led Cyras Systems from $15M to over $5B in valuation in 12 months with 3 rounds of VC funding, finally selling the company to Ciena in 2000. Stephen is currently Chairman of Denver-based Innovation Pavilion, a leader in entrepreneurial campuses and neighborhoods for millennial workers in suburban cities around the U.S. Previously as Executive VP of Bay Networks, Stephen led the $9B merger with Nortel. Stephen is an active Venture Capital investor and is a Board Director for several public and private companies and non-profit organizations. 

Robert (Bob) is a Board Director for several public companies including Aviat Networks (NASDAQ: AVNW), Ameri Holdings (OTC:AMRH), Novation Companies (OTC:NOVC), and Crossroads Systems (NASDAQ:CRDS) where Bob currently serves as Chairman. Bob is a leader in corporate strategy and corporate development in the technology industry. He served as VP of Strategy and Corporate Development for Hewlett-Packard and later as VP of Strategy for NetApp. Bob led the strategy for NetApp's 20%+ annual growth over his tenure which placed the company into the F500. Bob resides in Saratoga, California.

Description: Pilot Mountain Ventures is a seed stage venture capital firm, based out of New York City but investing globally in opportunities where we can add value. Our team is comprised of successful investors, corporate officers, consultants, and entrepreneurs with over fifty years combined experience. Our target investment is in the seed round, but we will invest up to through the Series A. While we are industry agnostic, we focus in technology and medical device where our partners have the most experience. Besides a financial investment, Pilot Mountain adds value that enables seed stage companies to hit the growth they need, through our business development partners, strategic advice, and recruiting network. We also help get you to that next funding round. We like scalable businesses, with low costs, and foreseeable exits. And we like investing in people solving real problems. We like visionaries, with determinate views of the future. We like when those visions serve to disrupt existing markets and create new ones. And while we believe in the importance of product and market, we believe most importantly in founders and teams. We prefer founding teams to solo founders, and we prefer successful serial entrepreneurs most of all. We establish relationships with our founders. We don't perform transactions with them. Shoot us an email if you want to hear more.

Description: Triton's initial investments typically range from $500,000 to $4 million, depending upon the needs of the company. We support portfolio companies as they make progress with additional follow-on investments, and we are often involved in introducing other investors to the company or in leading investment syndicates. In deciding which companies to fund among the hundreds we encounter, we tend to focus on three key considerations: Will the company's technology-based product or service significantly change the way business is conducted? Is there a large and/or rapidly growing market, manageable competition and moderate capital requirements? Is there a "positively charged" management team with experience and enthusiasm that we will feel good about working with even when things do not go according to plan? If the answer to all three questions is yes, we will definitely have an interest.

Description: Syndicated Communications Inc (Syncom), was founded in February 1977, with a mission to diversify the ownership of media in the United States. With that vision in mind, investments made by Syncom have fueled the growth of many successful companies, a number of which have become market leaders including BET, Radio One, TV One, and most recently Iridium Satellite. Today, Syncom Venture Partners is aggressively focused on creating the next generation of market leaders within the rapidly growing sectors of digital media, mobile technology, and web based services. We bring the unique, hands on perspective that comes with witnessing the emergence, and now the transformation of traditional, distribution centric media to the digital, content and technology centric media we are presently experiencing. Syncom's deep domain experience transcends this evolution and positions us to offer unparalleled guidance to our portfolio management teams as they navigate this complex environment.

Description: Mosley Ventures is a venture capital fund investing in early stage technology startups in Atlanta and the Southeast. We primarily invest in the following sectors - security software, mobility and wireless, big data and healthcare IT. Sig Mosley is the Managing Partner of Mosley Ventures. Since 1990, Sig has been the most prolific southeast investor in 122 startups with 83 liquidity events. Sig is currently the record holder of the largest southeast venture deal with the $5.7 billion acquisition of Tradex by Ariba. Mosley Ventures is a "for entrepreneur" fund as we invest in people. We believe in enabling founders to build their visions into successful companies. By practicing a high-touch discipline to develop the talent in entrepreneurs, our value creation begins prior to investing capital into the company. We analyze and validate market demand through collaborative efforts, weighing deeply on founder's domain expertise and vision. Our collaborative efforts also extend into the vast network of our syndicate partners. We have co-invested with most of the leading Venture Funds in the country, empowering our commitments to portfolio companies beyond seed or A round. Mosley Ventures is a nationally regarded expert in transforming technologies into sustainable companies; we dedicate our purpose to the success of entrepreneurs through the art and heart of working with brilliant talents.

Description: We are an early stage, post-seed/pre-Series A investment management firm, with an experienced team, all of whom have extensive cross-industry and cross-functional operating experience in software startups. We invest two crucial elements into early stage software companies - money and experience - to launch early stage companies to the next level. Many great early stage companies, which have raised initial seed capital to build v1 products and are now looking for a "pre-Series A" round, face a trade off between money and expertise. Individual Angel investors typically cannot identify, evaluate or help early-stage companies move forward, and traditional VC's invest at much later stages in a company's development. The Select team bridges the funding and expertise gap, with combined personal experience of more than 100 years of operating experience and over one billion dollars of successful exits. We are committed to using our personal resources, time, and network to help early stage companies succeed. Why do successful entrepreneurs pick us over others? Given our extensive and proven operating experience, we are able to form effective partnerships with successful entrepreneurs. Our commitment to entrepreneurs make us a "free" extension to the management team. We collectively have extensive experience in building robust technology, product management, outsourcing product development, strategic planning, early company structuring, revenue growth and management, and most importantly successful exits.

A single member of the group will normally serve on the Board of Directors of your company, but the resources of the entire group are available to you.

Description:
We are a fast-moving, intensely curious early-stage investment group. We seek exceptional, inspired founders from around the world who will set the course for ground-breaking innovation in mobility, security, and the future of flight. Our vision is to continuously ignite interest in the wonder that is aerospace.

Airbus is in our DNA, from our legacy of innovation and industry expertise to our global network. It is an asset to every company we fund, if and when they want it. Yet we operate with autonomy and trust, from the investments we make to the technologies they develop; we independently support entrepreneurs with unique ideas, plans, and structures. We are headquartered in Silicon Valley and Paris and fund start-ups across the globe. We are a valuable, efficient, and energetic partner to those who recognize that advances in aerospace will impact all life on Earth and beyond.

We welcome hearing from founders working hard to transform any facet of our industry. From urban air mobility, to connected fleets, to digital development and manufacturing, to advanced energy and propulsion. Quite literally, there is no limit.

We have particular expertise in clean technology, high tech (hardware and software), manufacturing, financial services, branded media, payments, and real estate.

Description: Technology & Marketing Ventures, Inc., through its Electronic-Boardroom TMV® Division, markets integrated research, consulting services, and information products to corporations and educational institutions. All Oxford University Conference participants were eligible to be on the Electronic-Boardroom TMV® Advisory Committee On Social Values, and to receive a password to the Electronic-Boardroom TMV® Web-site. T&MV Inc. hosts the site and provides tailored methodologies and programs, in order to continue collaboration on needed solutions to boardroom issues. At two other sesssions, Ms. Klein used her business professional model and university funding model to link other aspects of the boardroom to business and to education. · CHOOSING A SECOND CAREER USING TMVI PROFESSIONAL MODEL - Ms. Klein shared her own "long-term employability solutions" in a seminar originally conducted for New York University's federated alumni association. She uses the TMVI methodology to continually balance the relationships between social values and work experiences within a global economy. · HOW BUSINESS EDUCATION QUANTITATIVELY BENEFITS CAREER, COMPANY & STATE USING TMVI JOINT FUNDING MODEL - Ms. Klein discussed "win-win" venture experiences in a paper originally presented to the Council of Governing Boards, the Commission of Independent Colleges and Universities, and the New York State Governor's office. NYS Universities contribute $30 billion to the economic impact of NYS and constitute an industry. Further, if you are the one who sits on a three-legged stool (education, business and government), each is an equally important leg of a model solution for higher education/public policy/creative financing.
